id: pm-6l17
title: list/search --tags hard-refuses (exit 2) while create --tag auto-corrects — accept --tags as a never-block alias
description: "agent-UX audit F4: read commands use --tag, write commands use --tags; only create/update degrade gracefully. list --tags returns 'Refusing to auto-correct' exit 2 (dead-end). Accept --tags as a single-value alias on list/search (never-block) or downgrade the refusal to a warn + run corrected."
type: Issue
status: in_progress
priority: 2
tags[3]: agent-ux,"area:cli",never-block
created_at: "2026-06-07T17:04:17.473Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-07T21:31:56.161Z"
assignee: codex-agent-ux-reliability-20260607
author: maintainer-agent
parent: pm-mpbb
comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-07T19:58:21.266Z",codex-agent-ux-reliability-20260607,"Execution kickoff: duplicate-check confirms this remains the canonical open read-command alias issue. Implementing --tags never-block alias behavior in list/search with parser/contracts/completion parity."
  "2026-06-07T20:09:06.452Z",codex-agent-ux-reliability-20260607,"Implemented never-block alias behavior for read commands: list/search now treat --tags as a declared alias for --tag through CLI flag contracts and command registration, so bootstrap normalization resolves via flag_alias instead of flag_typo/retry refusal. Added completion parity for alias value suggestions in bash/zsh/fish and regression coverage in bootstrap/help-runtime/completion specs. Targeted verification passed (3 files, 200 tests)."
  "2026-06-07T20:47:40.797Z",codex-agent-ux-reliability-20260607,"Docs/contracts sync evidence: docs now explicitly describe list/search --tags alias behavior; contracts snapshot refreshed and current after alias additions."
  "2026-06-07T21:31:56.161Z",codex-agent-ux-reliability-20260607,"Verification evidence: manual temp-project dogfood validated list/search --tags alias path end-to-end in CLI with compact projection enabled; targeted regression suites and full coverage pass."
